        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                <date>Novbr 14/64.</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <sic>
                    <addressee>Revd I. Leesser</addressee>
                </sic>
            </p>
            <p>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Enclosed you will find a draft<lb/> for $14.00. I can not find your
                bill, but<lb/> according to my calculation, it can not exceed<lb/> this amount,
                should I however be mistaken<lb/> please let me know it and I will immediate˶<lb/>ly
                send you the difference. All what I have<lb/> of you yet are the <add>ה'
                    חומשים</add> which are not yet sold<lb/> because the man who ordered them, has
                like<lb/> many <del>like</del> from here, left for
                <placeName>Matamoras</placeName><lb/> and has not yet returned. The
                    <add>תפילות</add> are already<lb/> paid, and I could again use two as I had<lb/>
                before, also one with a <sic>german</sic> translation, and<lb/> 3 doz. of
                    <persName>Peixotto's</persName> Scriptures; I do not care<lb/> if you take your
                commission on <persName>Peixotto's</persName><lb/> books, only send them to me
                immediately on<lb/> receipt of this. Have you <del>all</del> already printed<lb/> my
                last letter, and expressed your ideas<lb/> on the subject? How are you? how have</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>you been since I last heard from<lb/> you? How does the Occident get<lb/> along? Has
                    <persName>Bondy</persName> been elected by the Cong.<lb/> R S.?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Hoping that these lines will find<lb/> you in the best health, and
                that you will<lb/> give my commission a quick attention<lb/> I remain dear Sir<lb/>
                most respectfully,<lb/> Yours,</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Dr J<add>?</add>y</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P. S./ Send me also 3 doz. of your<lb/> Hebrew Reader.</p>
        </body>
